{{Multiple issues|{{refimprove|date=December 2017}} {{no footnotes|date=December 2017}} {{COI|date=December 2017}}}} {{Infobox album | name = Dédié à toi (Monday Tuesday) | type = studio | artist = [[Dalida]] | cover = Dédié à toi cover.jpg | alt = | released = {{start date|1979}} | recorded = 1979 | venue = | studio = | genre = | length = | label = {{hlist|[[Orlando (label)|Orlando International Shows]]|[[Carrere Records|Carrere]]}} | producer = | prev_title = [[Génération 78 / Voilà pourquoi je chante / Ça me fait rêver]] | prev_year = 1978 | next_title = [[Gigi in Paradisco (album)|Gigi in Paradisco]] | next_year = 1980 }}
'''''Dédié à toi (Monday Tuesday)''''' is a French studio album released by [[Dalida]] in 1979.
== Background == {{unreferenced section|date=October 2011}} In this album, Dalida sings once more [[Jacques Brel]]'s "[[Quand on n'a que l'amour]]". She also memorializes her late lover [[Luigi Tenco]] through a cover of one of his masterpieces, "Vedrai vedrai". It includes her hit{{Citation needed|date=October 2011}} "[[Monday, Tuesday... Laissez-moi danser]]", and a patriotic homage to her birth country Egypt, "[[Helwa ya balady]]".
The album proved to be one of Dalida's most successful albums of the seventies, selling millions of copies.{{Citation needed|date=December 2017}}
